//Question: Read the below code and pick correct option?


public class Test {
  public void main(String[] args) { 
    int x = 6;
    Test test = new Test();
    test.doSomething(x);
    System.out.print(" main x = " + x);
  }
void doSomething(int x) {
    System.out.print(" method x = " + x++);
  }
}


Output :-
A. An exception is thrown at runtime
B. method x = 6, main x = 6
C. method x = 6 main x = 7
D. method x = 7 main x = 6

Answer:Option A
Explanation:Main method is not static in class Test , define the main method as :public static void main(String[] args)
